Package de.rwth.swc.coffee4j.model.converter

Class IndexBasedModelConverter

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.rwth.swc.coffee4j.model.converter.IndexBasedModelConverter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ModelConverter
    public class IndexBasedModelConverter
extends java.lang.Object
implements ModelConverter
    A ModelConverter based on using the indices of supplied Parameter and Value. This means that the first parameter in the list of InputParameterModel.getParameters() is translated to 0, the second one to 1 and so on and so fourth. The same is done with values per parameter. These integers are then used for TupleList and Combination, so [0, 1] is a combination where the first parameter is mapped to it's first value and the second one to its second value.
